This dataset includes files that the POSMV Navigation computer logged onboard the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Healy during the BEST 2009 0901 (early spring) cruise. The data are from various navigation devices and from devices related to the Seabeam system. There are also event files in this dataset that are from various systems. The event files show the start and stop times and various events in the recording and setup history of the device. The individual data files are collected into tar files by day. The following is a list of the devices: 
adu5 - Ashtech GPS data;
aggps - Trimble AGGPS data;
ais - Automatic Identification System messages;
bgm221 - BGM221 Gravimeter;
bgm222 - BGM222 Gravimeter;
ibs_waypoints - Bridge IBS Navigation System Way Points data;
mk27 - MK27 Sperry Gyroscope data;
mk39 - MK39 Sperry Gyroscope data;
posatt - POSMV Attitude data;
posnav - POSMV GPS data;
posreform2sb - Reformatted POSMV data for Seabeam;
sbctr - Seabeam center beam data;
sbsv - Seabeam surface sound velocity data;
tsg_met - SIO TSG and Met sensor data;
winch_aft - Aft A Frame winch data;
winch_stbd - Starboard A Frame winch data

This dataset includes data from the Knudsen 320B/R Depth Sounder system onboard the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Healy during the Bering Sea Ecosystem Study (BEST) 2009 0902 (late spring) cruise. The Knudsen depth sounder records the 3 - 6 kHz data (Sub Bottom Profile) underway. The individual data files have been collected into tar files by day. The following is a list of the file extensions and their meaning for the data files contained in the tar files: 
.keb - Binary Knudsen Playback File;
.kea - ASCII log of depth, settings and environmental data;
.sgy - Binary SEG-Y extended Seismic format

